What I am getting at is that most bullied have been bullied and do not know how to get the help for it.

Which is why community is so important because that is where the accountability and reprogramming can begin.

Even then though; one has to be able to see their behavior as..

author: Suzette
text:
Most bullies do not perceive their behavior as wrong or hurting because it was done onto them.

Like noted earlier >>> ‘man’ doesn’t acknowledge the ways in which his/her/ they behavior is effecting another because they monopolize off of it. (Satisfaction of the ego) THREAD

author: Suzette
text:
Which I why I move the way I do in this world>> with so much love.

I am equally aware though of the accountability one needs to have in order to Heal. (As I have had to take initiative to heal myself) 

With this being said (thread)

author: Suzette
text:
I was never weak. I was stronger than them mentally, physically, spiritually and emotionally. Which I believe triggered them into believing they had to beat me down…

Don’t get me wrong I completely am aware of mental health and the effects of the unconscious mind… (thread)

author: Suzette
text: I truly believe that ‘bullies’ are formed out of pain bodies (ego). Many of the bullies I experienced were hurting deeply and didn’t know who to go to for that hurt. So guess what? They came to the ones they ‘thought’ were weak… I must say. Even as someone who has been bullied…

author: Suzette
text:
What makes anyone think they have the power to define ones life for them?

As a young child, I could never understand why I was picked on by family, friends and teachers.. (I understand now) >> they couldn’t find their infinite light, so they tried to dim mine. 

(Thread)

author: Suzette
text:
Our world >> let me be clear ‘man’ has monopolized on hurting people and making individuals suffer to continue this loop. If we continue to hurt people, we as a collective will continue to hurt. Everyone looks different WHO ARE YOU TO TELL ONE THEY AREN’T ENOUGH?
(Thread)

author: Suzette
text:
Just saw a billboard on the Highway that stated.

As someone who has been through many traumatic experiences of being bullied. I ask that the collective please take a step back and put yourself in another shoes. (Thread)
